# Types of Two Pointers

## 1. Opposite Direction Pointers

```java
int left = 0;
int right = n - 1;
```

Used in:
- Pair Sum
- Triplet Sum
- Quadruplet Sum
- Sorted Arrays

---

## 2. Same Direction Pointers

```java
int slow = 0;
int fast = 0;
```

Used in:
- Remove Duplicates
- Remove Elements
- Partition Array

---

## 3. Fast & Slow Pointers

```java
ListNode slow = head;
ListNode fast = head;
```

Used in:
- Detect Cycle
- Find Middle Node
- Palindrome Linked List

---

# Pattern 1: Pair Sum

### Condition
- Sorted Array
- Find two numbers whose sum = target

```java
while(left < right) {

    int sum = arr[left] + arr[right];

    if(sum == target)
        return true;

    else if(sum < target)
        left++;

    else
        right--;
}
```

### Complexity

```text
Time  : O(n)
Space : O(1)
```

---

# Pattern 2: Triplet Sum

### Condition
- Sorted Array
- Find three numbers

```java
for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

    int left = i + 1;
    int right = n - 1;

    while(left < right) {

        // logic
    }
}
```

### Complexity

```text
Time  : O(n²)
Space : O(1)
```

---

# Pattern 3: Quadruplet Sum

### Condition
- Sorted Array
- Find four numbers

```java
for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

    for(int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

        int left = j + 1;
        int right = n - 1;

        while(left < right) {

            // logic
        }
    }
}
```

### Complexity

```text
Time  : O(n³)
Space : O(1)
```

